Secret service discloser Edward Snowden is fundamentally ready for a conversation with German authorities.
First he wants to know, however, his situation clearedly.
The former NSA-employee searched by the USA explained that in a not addressed writing which the greens-politician Hans-Christian Ströbele published on Friday after a meeting with Snowden and passed on to Federal Government, Bundestag and general Federal Government attorney.
The writing has following wording according to a translation spread by Ströbele:
